Create a ParameterizedQueryImpl object.

Parameters:
typeName - the type of object being queried
foreignTypeName - the type of object by which to query
sqlTableName - the name of the SQL table corresponding to the queried object type
name - the association end (property) name in the foreign class
associationTypeName - for a many-to-many association, the association class name; otherwise, null
sqlLinkingTableName - for a many-to-many association, the SQL table name for the association class; otherwise, null
linksPropertyName - the name of the collection property that contains the links (objects of the association class type)
foreignPackageName - the name of the package of the type of object by which to query
packageName - the name of the package that contains the type of the queried object(s)
associationPackageName - the name of the package that contains the association type (linking table type)
queriedCols - a collection of SELECT-list column names
keyCols - a collection of foreign key column names
subsystem - the subsystem in which to define the query class
joinCols - a collection of ON-clause column names
queriedLinkCols - a collection of SELECT-list column names from the association-class table
linkKeyCols - the key columns from the association class used to query the association class by the associated class key
associationDto - the DTO that represents the linking table
associatedDto - the DTO that represents the associated class (the class of the object being queried)
linksSubsystem - the subsystem that contains the linking association class
dto - the DTO that represents the querying object
manyKeyCols - the ordered list of association class key columns used to query objects from one associated class by the key of the other associated class

getLinksWhereExpr

public java.lang.String getLinksWhereExpr()
Description copied from class: ParameterizedQuery

Get the WHERE clause expression for the association links QueryBy SQL statement. This consists of the link key columns associated with the parameterized query. These should be the key column names for the specific property that correspond to the primary key in the associated object for this query. So, if AB links A and B, and this is the property on A, the key should be the column names in AB that refer to the columns in A. For a recursive association (AA), this would be the particular key columns in AA that link to the particular association end in A.

Specified by:
getLinksWhereExpr in class ParameterizedQuery
See Also:
ParameterizedQuery.getLinksWhereExpr()

getManyToManyWhereExpr

public java.lang.String getManyToManyWhereExpr()
Description copied from class: ParameterizedQuery

Get the WHERE clause expression for the many-to-many objects QueryBy SQL statement. If A links to B through association C, and you want to get the set of Bs linked to an A, you query the set of B objects joined to C objects where the A key of the C object is the same as the A key of the current A object. The where clause thus contains the key attributes for the A key.

Specified by:
getManyToManyWhereExpr in class ParameterizedQuery

getManyToManyFromClause

public java.lang.String getManyToManyFromClause()
Description copied from class: ParameterizedQuery

Get the FROM clause expression for the many-to-many objects QueryBy SQL statement. If A links to B through association C, and you want to get the set of Bs linked to an A, you query the set of B objects joined to C objects where the A key of the C object is the same as the A key of the current A object. The FROM clause thus contains the association table C as well as the associated table A and any subclass tables of A.

Specified by:
getManyToManyFromClause in class ParameterizedQuery

generateColumnLists

public void generateColumnLists()
Generate the lists of queried columns, key columns, and queried association columns. You can call this method multiple times; whenever there are properties, the internal collection gets set and after that does not change, so you can attempt the generation as often as needed to get all the columns filled in.
